@node "Introduction" "Introduction   "
                               Introduction
                               ------------

    CoolMod is a Multiformat MUI Module player.  I programmed the first 
    version one day, simply out of curiosity, to see if I could do it.  
    The first version was very crude, only played a module and it kind of 
    went on from there.  I then went on and coded a Gadtools GUI and then 
    started implementing new features.  

    Now further on, I felt that Gadtools didn't do what I wanted, besides 
    Joe asked me to change it to MUI.  So I read up on MUI, and 
    programmed it.  MUI is so much nicer!!!

    TESTED ON:
    ----------

    * A1200 030 42mhz 6mb RAM Easy CDROM 420mb HD (My old sys!)
    * A1200 030 42mhz 6mb RAM SurfSquirrel CDROM 1.4gb HD
    * A1200T 030 50mhz 10mb RAM SurfSquirrel 2.1Gb HD
    * A1200 020 14mhz 2mb Chip RAM
    * A1200 020 28mhz 6mb RAM ZAPPO HD
    * A4000T 604 PPC 060 128mb RAM and CyberVision PPC.
    * A1200T 603e PPC 160MHz 040 50mb Ram
    * A1200T 603e PPC 240MHz 040 34mb Ram
    * A1200 040 25mhz 18MB Ram Easy CD 420mb HD (My NEW sys!)
@endnode

@node "requirements" "Requirements   "
                               Requirements
                               ------------

    CoolMod V1.52 needs:

    * An Amiga computer :)

    * Reqtools.library

    * Play16 (to play samples - installed in the default path)

    * Playsid.library (to play SidTunes)

    * MUI.  Not sure what version but it works with 3.8 :)


         If you need any of this, you can download it from our website:

                     http://ireland.amiga.org/emerald
@endnode

@node "features" "   Features   "
                                 Features
                                 --------

    CoolMod is stacked full of nice features:

    * A lovely MUI interface.

    * The ability to play :
        Pro/Noise/Sound Tracker modules
        OctaMed/Med modules (Limited support but BACK IN!!!!)
        Sid tunes (C64 type noise files)
        IFF 8SVX *
        AIFF * 
        RIFF WAVE * 
        Sun AUDIO *
    
    NB: To play samples, Play16 is required.  Thanks go to Thomas Wenzel 
    for this cracking program.

    * Executable only around 80k, very small. (But getting bigger :()

    * Essentially free, send me an email and I will send you a keyfile
      to get rid of those requesters!!

    * CPU Friendly.  Doesn't eat stacks of CPU time or RAM.

    * Lovely Help bubbles now and a revised text box!! V1.64

    * The Ability to switch on and off Channels (Pt Only) from version
      V1.67

    * OCTAMED / MED make it back into the program.  Very limited at the
      minute though.
@endnode

